Shanghai. China (April I, 1920?. 13? Szec\nhuen Road. Manager, Mr. Henry S. DeVault.\nfrom their new york staff.\nHavana. Cuba (July 1, 1920). National\nBank:of Cuba Building. Manager. Mr. Julian\nl. barnett. from their new york staff.\nParis. France (July 1, 1920). 49 Rue de\nProvence. Manager. Mr. Howard P. Garner,\nfrom their new york staff and latterly\nChief Accountant for the United States\nLiquidation Commission.\nJULY 1, 192a\n6% PRUDENCE-BONDS\nThe Strongest Example of the\nStrongest Type of Security\nA BOND backed by first mort?\ngages on selected income\nproducing real estate is the strong?\nest type of security there is, outside\nof a United States Government\nBond. And Prudence-Bonds are\nthe strongest example of the type.\nBacked by great and growing\nequities in income producing\nproperties.\nBacked again by the credit and\nreputation of the borrower.\nAnd backed finally by a guaran?\ntee which pledges every dollar of\nour resources for the protection\nof our bondholders, Prudence\nBonds are acknowledged by finan?\ncial authorities to be unique in\ntheir impenetrable security.\nWE PAY THE 4% NORMAL FEDERAL INCOME TAX\nSend for Booklet 0-13\nRealty Associates\nInvestment Corporation\n31 Nassau St., New York Phone Rector 2181\n162 Remscn St, Brooklyn Phone Main 6480\nPRUDENCE-BONDS ABE ISSUED IN DE?\nNOMINATIONS OF $100. ?500 AND $1,000.\nGUARANTY TRUST COMPANY OF NEW YORK\nTrustees of This Issue.\nTHE LEXINGTON AVE. and PAVONIA\nFERRY RAILROAD COMPANY\nTo the Holders of the\nFirst Mortgage Five Per Cent. Gold Bonds of THE LEXING?\nTON AVENUE AND PAVONIA FERRY RAILROAD\nCOMPANY, dated August 24th, 1893:\nDefault having been made in the payment of the interest falling\ndue March 1st, 1920, on the bonds of the above mentioned issue,\nthe undersigned, at the request of the holders of a large amount\nof said bonds, have consented to act as a Bondholders' Pro?\ntective Committee.\nIn the judgment of the Committee it is expedient and neces?\nsary for the holders of such bonds to unite for the mutual protec?\ntion of their interests in view of the existing default, and to that\nend the Committee invites the holders of said bonds to deposit\nthe same, accompanied with the coupons falling due March 1st,\n1920, and all subsequent coupons, on or before SEPTEMBER 3,\n1920. with CENTRAL UNION TRUST COMPANY OF NEW\nYORK, No, 80 Broadway, New York City, as Depositary under\na Deposit Agreement which is now in course of preparation.\nAgainst such deposits the Depositary will issue its Certificate?\nof Deposit under said Deposit Agreement\nCopies of the Deposit Agreement may be obtained, when\nprepared, from the Depositary.\nNew York, July 12, 1920.\nF. J. FULLER,\nVlcc-Presldent of Central Union\nTrust Company of New York.\nA. R. H0RR.\nVIce-Preeldent of The Equitable\nLife Assurance Society of the\nUnited States.\nREGINALD FOSTER,\nALEXANDER GREEN General Counsel. New Kng-land\n,ln Mutual I.lle Insurance Com\n^T^ Broadway, N. T. City P'ny' BoBton' M*~\nCENTRAL UNION TRUST COMPANY committee\nOF NEW YORK CHARLES E. SIGLER\nDepositary, S??-.retary,\n80 Broadway, N. T. City. No. 80 Broadway, 3g. y. CUr.","height":"25365","width":"20070"}}
